cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper involves the development and evaluation of a deep neural network controller for autonomous driving, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of Bayesian neural networks, which are a type of probabilistic machine learning model, indicating a potential fit for the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The use of sensors and image processing for autonomous driving also suggests a potential fit for computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the safety guarantees and decision making involved in autonomous driving, indicating a potential fit for systems and control (cs.SY).
